GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 1001
Short Title: Reports Related to Sexual Assault Exams. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Johnson-Hostler and Campbell (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Health, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 14, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT REQUIRING PROGRAMS APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF NURSING THAT
3 TRAIN SEXUAL ASSAULT NURSE EXAMINERS TO ANNUALLY REPORT
4 CERTAIN INFORMATION.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 2.(a) Article 9A of Chapter 90 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
7 a new section to read:
8 "§ 90-171.38A. Sexual assault nurse examiners data collection.
9 On October 1 of each year, programs approved by the Board under G.S. 90-171.38 to train,
10 educate, and credential sexual assault nurse examiners shall annually report to the Board
11 information on all graduates from each program. This report shall include the number of total
12 graduates, the county of employment of each graduate, and, if known, where each graduate plans
13 to work or is employed."
14 SECTION 2.(b) The North Carolina Board of Nursing may adopt rules to implement
15 the provisions of this act.
16 SECTION 2.(c) This act becomes effective August 1, 2025.
*H1001-v-1*

